long_desc.thetext:
Simple case is clear.

  q("#warning").setStyle("display", "none");
  q("#warning").setStyle("display", "block");

goes

  q("#warning").hide();
  q("#warning").show();


But it conflicts with qx.ui.core.Widget's naming,
its "exclude" acts like this q("#warning").hide(), and "hide" is about
"visibility" style. So it's getting less clear, and it's good to rethink
considering full qx.ui.core.Widget's
show/hide/exclude/isVisible/isHidden/isExcluded and Sizzle's ":visible"
pseudo-class.

Originated from #6581.
